n><br> <font color=#333399>(6/21/01 8:17:54 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dealing with VI</span><hr size=1> I've had dealings with CS, Gms, and guides.<br>
<br>
At least 6 times.<br>
<br>
Each time, they were EXTREMELY polite, and very helpful.<br>
<br>
Once to report that a quest mob was bugged. GM checked, sure enough my items had vanished. GM replaced items, and apologized. No muss, no fuss. Took 15 minutes.<br>
<br>
Got trapped under the world once in that &quot;zoning in Unrest&quot; bug and fell and fell. GM got me out and fixed me. Took about 20-30 minutes. Body was gone, no prob.<br>
<br>
Recently, as a test to see if all the bitching and moaning I hear on the boards was true, I tried an experiment. I reported missing NPCs in Kael twice, and twice via e-mail. One time a guide checked into it, one time a GM. Both times they said yes there was a problem, and that it was being looked at. Each e-mail was responded to by CS rep, and they politely referred me to Ester the Testers' In Development page.<br>
<br>
And, 2 nights ago, in Dragon NEcropolis, a 2nd group who was sort of with us died, and forgot what they did to bodies. Or, forgot where they died. No necros would come summon. They petitoned. Not one but 2 GMs appeared, chatted with us at zone (we had to succor). Remembering my recent test, I figured I'd try the question about NPCs again. GM paused for a bit, and returned and informed me that it was being repaired.<br>
<br>
     So- each time I have had a problem, and have been polite in asking, I personally have never had a bad experience with a VI rep. They assisted me, and they answered my questions. What more can I ask for? This was in the process of normal day-to-day casual gaming. <br>
<br>
Ok, this wasn't power gaming, and it wasn't a big raid in a so-called &quot;uber&quot; zone against an &quot;uber&quot; mob.<br>
<br>
But that being said, there are a lot of us who DO have problems in the normal course a gaming session who DO get help when needed. There are also &quot;uber&quot; guilds who are successful in these areas who have been able to do so without bad experiences with GMs (Paradigm on Sol Ro for example). <br>
<br>
So, as fun and satisfying as it is to repeatedly bash a faceless enitity, or &quot;The MAn,&quot; (ie- Verant), remember that there ARE people how there who have had good experiences. I don't care how many people complain. One angry guild or a few angry people on a public BBS is NOT indicitive of a population of 300,000+.<br>
<br>
Just a little perspective for you.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
