<br>
I can't remember when was the last time I called a Guide/GM in game.  I find it more relaxing and less stressful to simply lick my wounds and go on even If I THINK it was bug.  I have had items poofing while zoning, bags disappearing while trading and never got anything replaced. However, that has never been my beef with VI.<br>
<br>
My problem has been that it virtually impossible to resolve small problems via email.  I posted earlier that I had been billed for 6 accounts although I owned only 5.  I sent out email to correct this and got caught in a loop of emails for about 5 weeks.  I would supply all the information and they would ask for more. I would do it again and get the identical &quot;canned&quot; email back.<br>
<br>
I finally called LONG DISTANCE from overseas and stayed 45 minutes on hold to discuss the problem. It was solved in 5 minutes and I had indeed the pleasure to talk to a very polite young man.  However, the billing reappeared the following month.  During the same converstaion, I tried to update the REGISTRATION information and I was told that it was not possible but that this information was not relevant.  The CST informed me that the original information or the original CD key was not important for maintaining your account.  Well, that was obviously WRONG information as in case of a lost pw, VI will send a new one to the REGISTERED email - versus the current one in your station info. Good luck to talk your way out of that mess!<br>
<br>
This is an example of CST mismanagement. VI should have all this billing information ONLINE and allow people to make changes to THEIR personal information.  Oh well, I almost forgot that, according, to VI's vision, we lost the right to our personal life when we signed up for EQ. <br>
<br>
WE ALL BELONG TO VERANT!   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ublackwulf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Blackwulf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/21/01 10:09:45 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Dealing with VI</span><hr size=1> That's nice, Dreth1, but many of us have had just the opposite experience.<br>
<br>
Time and again, veRant's laughable idea of customer service has been rude, inconsistently and apathetic.<br>
<br>
I could dig out screenshots of GMs telling me that they knew all the bugs and that therefor I didn't die to a bug (anyone remember dying to the quest giver on sister isle in OOT?  The one that attacked you for killing pirates near her, when the quest she gave was to kill pirates?  That was fixed not long ago, but that was months too late for me).<br>
<br>
Or GMs giving warnings, and promising emails to document it, which never were sent (and yes, my email is kept current).<br>
<br>
Or the head GM on the server taking TWO POINT FIVE MONTHS to respond to emails (I emailed weekly, ended up posting the entire set of forwarded emails to the CS forums, and it still took them another two weeks to get Shiften to get around to blowing me off.)<br>
<br>
Or Buggy quests that eat the items, and the lack of response from VCSR (the KML quest in GD, I've done it, SO went to do it and the mob that drops the leggings never spawned in any form, the rest of the quest went fine.  Guide responding said he'd escalate the issue to the server GM, who responded to my email with 'Sorry, never heard about it, won't do anything about it, have a nice day')<br>
<br>
Petitions never answered, or responded to 6 hours later with a 'Hi, friend!  Hope your problem worked out okay!'  Funny thing, if someone is shouting obscenities at the zone, they respond in minutes to the /report &amp; /petition.  (Try it sometime, /petition that someone is emoting sexual acts, or shouting same at the zone.  Less than 5 minutes later, you will get a response.  /petition about losing your body when a zombie climbs onto the boat in Erud's Crossing, and see how many _days it takes them to respond)<br>
<br>
And no, I don't start out rude to CS, that's silly.  There is no point in aggrevating people you are hoping to get assistance from, particularly when they may have no hand in making policy, or no choice in how to respond.<br>
<br>
veRant CS has a reputation of considering 'customer = liar', 'customer = thief', 'customer = enemy', _for _a _reason.  This wasn't collective 'sour grapes', it was a realization based on _thousands of encounters.  <br>
<br>
Sure, there may well be as many good encounters as bad, but that doesn't excuse veRant CS. <br>
<br>
As things stand, I only bother to contact VCS to get a merchant killed and returned to his bind point, that's the thing they can seem to do with any speed.  And I wholeheartedly agree with the two points brought up in this thread:  Respond to veRant CS as you would hostile airport security, and _never admit anything that can be misconstrued against you.<br>
<br>
Oh, and all the (examples) above are taken from my personal experience, and are just the ones I pulled off the top of my head, I could post a frigging phone sized set of examples, all witnessed first hand, or at most told to me by people I trust who had it happen to them.  The number of times I've actually gotten a useful response to my problem has been .... 3.  6 if you count having a merchant killed, and one of those 3 was a response that made me happy and would have gotten the guide fired if I were stupid enough to post the details where veRant could read them.  Been playing since May of '99, the game has a lot going for it, its just the people behind it that are the problem.<br>
